&lt;!doctype html&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;grid&quot;&gt; &lt;!-- Left column: main content --&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;panel&quot;&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Executive Summary&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;muted small&quot;&gt; POLKUS (PRedictive Operational Leverage &amp; Knowledge Utility System) — observed as a black-box predictive engine that ingests social, economic and media telemetry to propose targeted policy moves and information interventions. This page documents reproducible artifacts, simplified model forms, and a small set of anonymized statistics derived from intercepted test data. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;panel&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:12px;&quot;&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Model — Simplified Mathematical Form&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;small muted&quot;&gt; Below are the simplified equations used to approximate POLKUS behaviour for investigative analysis. These are intentionally reduced forms (not production code). &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;small&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:8px;&quot;&gt; &lt;strong&gt;1. Sentiment influence kernel (continuous-time):&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;div style=&quot;margin-top:6px;&quot; class=&quot;small&quot;&gt; \\[ I(t) = \int_{-\infty}^{t} K(t - \tau)\, S(\tau)\, d\tau \\] &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;muted small&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:6px;&quot;&gt; where \(S(\tau)\) is aggregate social signal (volume × polarity) and \(K(\cdot)\) a decaying influence kernel. &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;small&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:10px;&quot;&gt; &lt;strong&gt;2. Policy impact score (discrete):&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;small&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:6px;&quot;&gt; \\[ P_{c,t} = \sigma\!\Big( w_1 I_t + w_2 E_{c,t} + w_3 D_{c,t} + b\Big) \\] &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;muted small&quot;&gt; where \(P_{c,t}\) = predicted compliance in constituency \(c\) at time \(t\); \(E\)=economic indicator vector, \(D\)=demographic features; \(\sigma\) = logistic. &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;small&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:10px;&quot;&gt; &lt;strong&gt;3. Control objective (optimization view):&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;small&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:6px;&quot;&gt; \\[ \min_{\theta}\; \sum_{c,t} \ell\big( y_{c,t}, P_{c,t}(\theta) \big) + \lambda \|\theta\|_2^2 \\] &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;muted small&quot;&gt;Loss \(\ell\) = cross-entropy of desired vs observed behaviours; \(\theta\) parameters of the action policy generator.&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;panel&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:12px;&quot;&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Pseudocode — Action Selection Module&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;pre class=&quot;code&quot;&gt; POLKUS: simplified action-selection pseudocode (investigative reimplementation) # procedure SELECT_ACTIONS(state, budget): inputs: state = {I_t, E_t, D_c}, budget (resource limit) candidates = GENERATE_STRATEGIES(state) for each strategy s in candidates: score[s] = PREDICT_IMPACT(s, state) - COST(s) sorted = SORT_DESC(score) chosen = [] cost = 0 for s in sorted: if cost + COST(s) &lt;= budget: chosen.append(s) cost += COST(s) return chosen &lt;p class=&quot;small muted&quot;&gt;Notes: GENERATE_STRATEGIES() includes information ops, policy nudges, payment targets, and ad-placement schedules (simplified for analysis).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;panel&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:12px;&quot;&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Key Statistics (anonymized test extract)&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;table&gt; &lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Metric&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Value (test net)&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Notes&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/thead&gt; &lt;tbody&gt; &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Prediction horizon&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;14 days&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;rolling window (median)&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt; &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Mean AUC (behavioural classifier)&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;0.81&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;test-0 holdout&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt; &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Average influence uplift&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;+6.4%&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;measured on synthetic cohorts&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt; &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;False positive rate&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;12.3%&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;tuned for recall&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt; &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Data sources&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Social, Search, Mobility, Consumption&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;aggregated &amp;amp; anonymized&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt; &lt;/tbody&gt; &lt;/table&gt; &lt;div style=&quot;margin-top:10px;&quot; class=&quot;small muted&quot;&gt; These numbers are from a reconstructed testbed: they are realistic approximations for investigative use and not direct copies of any proprietary system. &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;!-- Right column: quick tools &amp; artifacts --&gt; &lt;aside&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;panel&quot;&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Quick Artifacts&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;pill&quot;&gt;Leaked memo&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pill&quot;&gt;Kernel sample&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pill&quot;&gt;Ad schedule&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;muted small&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:8px;&quot;&gt;Click any artifact to reveal a redacted preview (mocked for web demo).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;pre class=&quot;code&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:8px;&quot;&gt; &mdash; MEMO (redacted) &mdash; From: [REDACTED] To: SYNC NODE Subject: &ldquo;Targeted calming operation&rdquo; &hellip;ACTION: Increase local &lsquo;satisfaction&rsquo; indicators by +5% in W4. &hellip;FUNDS: allocate microgrants (masked) &lt;div class=&quot;panel&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:12px;&quot;&gt; &lt;h2&gt;ROC &amp;amp; Confusion (sample)&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;svg class=&quot;chart&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 300 160&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot; aria-hidden&gt; &lt;!-- simple ROC-like curve --&gt; &lt;defs&gt;&lt;linearGradient id=&quot;g&quot; x1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;stop offset=&quot;0&quot; stop-color=&quot;#e3b23c&quot; stop-opacity=&quot;0.9&quot;/&gt;&lt;stop offset=&quot;1&quot; stop-color=&quot;#7bd389&quot; stop-opacity=&quot;0.8&quot;/&gt;&lt;/linearGradient&gt;&lt;/defs&gt; &lt;rect x=&quot;0&quot; y=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;160&quot; fill=&quot;#071018&quot; rx=&quot;6&quot;/&gt; &lt;path d=&quot;M20,140 C80,60 160,30 280,20&quot; stroke=&quot;url(#g)&quot; stroke-width=&quot;3&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; stroke-linecap=&quot;round&quot;/&gt; &lt;line x1=&quot;20&quot; y1=&quot;140&quot; x2=&quot;280&quot; y2=&quot;140&quot; stroke=&quot;#112227&quot; stroke-width=&quot;1&quot;/&gt; &lt;text x=&quot;22&quot; y=&quot;152&quot; fill=&quot;#687a82&quot; font-size=&quot;10&quot;&gt;FPR →&lt;/text&gt; &lt;/svg&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;small muted&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:8px;&quot;&gt;Illustrative ROC curve for the behavioural classifier (AUC ≈ 0.81).&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;panel&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:12px;&quot;&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Investigator Notes&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;ul class=&quot;small muted&quot;&gt; &lt;li&gt;POLKUS uses a decaying kernel to weight fresh events.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Policy nudges scored via logistic impact proxy (P&lt;sub&gt;c,t&lt;/sub&gt;).&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;High recall goal; false positives exploited as leverage.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Recommendation: trace ad-buy IDs &amp;amp; payment microflows (50–200 tx nodes).&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/aside&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style=&quot;margin-top:14px;&quot; class=&quot;panel&quot;&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Algorithm Trace — Example (anonymized)&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;pre class=&quot;code&quot;&gt; Trace: single constituency action scoring (anonymized) # state = {I:0.73, E: -0.12, D: [age50pct:0.34, urban:0.7]} actions = [ad_burst, microgrant, rally_incentive] scores = { ad_burst: 0.42, microgrant: 0.55, rally_incentive: 0.22 } chosen = [microgrant, ad_burst] # budget limited -&gt; pick top2
Observed uplift (synthetic cohort): microgrant +3.8%, ad_burst +1.6% # &lt;/pre&gt; &lt;p class=&quot;small muted&quot;&gt;Note: This trace is a simplified investigative reimplementation — it is intentionally transparent to allow auditors to validate logic.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;footer&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;small muted&quot;&gt;Disclaimer: This page contains fictionalized and anonymized research examples for investigative storytelling. It is not a leak of real systems.&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/footer&gt;
